title: For Sale:  Femaru Model 37M .380
postcontent: I WANT TO MOVE THIS PISTOL OUT AND INTO THE HANDS OF A COLLECTOR OR SOMEONE WHO WILL APPRECIATE IT!I am selling my very rare and collectible 1941 FEMARU-FEGYVER-ES GEPGYAR R.T. 37M otherwise known as a Hungarian Femaru Model 37M.  I originally put this out locally and have decided to put it out nationally.I paid $275 for this pistol at an estate/garage sale plus $100 for an original magazine as the pistol only came with an aftermarket mag. (Which I would include).  The seller and myself knew nothing about this pistol and after doing extensive research, found out it's true value.  If you were to look at Gunbroker.com, GunsAmerica.com, the Blue Book or many of your on-line dealers, you would see these go for anywhere between $375-$600+ depending on condition.  The original mags alone cost $150-$200 now.  This pistol is now a fully authenticated 1941 Femaru 37M with the addition of the original mag.  The mag is probably going to need a new spring as the seller told me he broke off about 1" of the spring when he was restoring it.  I would probably take the spring out of the aftermarket mag and install that spring into the original mag.  As a note, in 1941 mags had no serial #'s.I am a shooter, not a collector and I shoot regularly at my local range.  After finding out the value of this pistol, I do not take this to the range anymore.  Naturally, it has been test fired and broken down and cleaned & oiled extensively.  It is remarkably accurate given it's fixed sights.  I own a host of pistols and do not need this lying around.  I put the condition of this pistol on the high side of 'good'. I am mainly looking to get back out of this what I have put into it.The pistol was designed by Frommer, a prominent Hungarian gun manufactrer in Budapest, Hungary and produced weapons for the Hungarian Army.  In 1929 Frommer originally produced the 29M which was superceded in 1937 by the 37M.  It is styled after the proven design of the Colt 1911 as most manufacturers did and still do.  This pistol was made in Budapest, Hungary in 1941 and used by the Hungarian Army until Nazi Germany occupied Hungary and renamed it 'Pistole 37(u)', the lower case (u) was used to signify it's Hungarian origin.  This pistol has NO Nazi markings as it is 'pre-war'.As you can see from the photo's showing the serial # and the dates of manufacture, this pistol is over 75 years old.  The caliber is .380acp and was referred to as 9mm Kurz(European).The .380 barrel is interchangeable with the 7.65 (.32acp) barrel as is the mag.  The 7.65 was produced by Femaru for the German Luftwaffe after occupation and an additional safety was installed at the rear of the slide.  The only safety on an original Femaru 37M such as this is a grip safety.I could go on and on about the history of the manfacturer etc., but my space is limited.  I also have many more photo's, but I'm only allowed 3 here.  If you need further info, more photo's, a specifc photo, or more intense docmentation, you can contact me through 'contact seller' at the top of the page or text me at REDACTED.  I am located in Spring Hill, FL.I am asking $425 and may possibly entertain a reasonable offer.  Cashier's check only.  No CC.  I do not want trades.  Receipt will be issued.  You would be responsible for the cost of shipping, any FFL fees if necessary, etc.  (NOTE: AT TOP OF LISTING IT SHOWS SHIP AS 'NO'.  I DON'T KNOW HOW TO MAKE IT 'YES'.)  I do not ship to California.
